### 🏥 MEDICAL DESIGN REQUIREMENTS

**Color Psychology for Medical Context:**
- Red (Oral): Warm, approachable, commonly associated with oral medications
- Blue (IV): Professional, sterile, clinical precision
- Purple (Both): Sophisticated, comprehensive coverage

**Northwestern Segment Color Coding Strategy:**
- MRSA: High-alert orange (resistant pathogen attention)
- VRE: Critical red (limited treatment options)  
- Anaerobes: Deep purple (unique treatment needs)
- Atypicals: Teal (distinct from standard bacteria)
- Pseudomonas: Warning amber (opportunistic alerts)
- Gram(-): Professional blue (common broad spectrum)
- MSSA: Safe green (treatable, positive outcomes)
- E. faecalis: Neutral gray-blue (standard care)

**Clinical Accessibility Priorities:**
1. <30 second emergency access to any clinical information
2. 4.5:1 contrast ratio minimum for all text/background combinations
3. Color-blind safe with pattern/texture backups
4. High-contrast mode for bright clinical environments
5. Touch-friendly 44px minimum target sizes

